SIMPLE: feme
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Feme
<hw>Feme</hw> <pr>(f⟦ecr⟧m <it>or</it> f⟦acr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OF. <ets>feme</ets>, F. <ets>femme</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Old
Law)</fld> <def>A woman.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Feme covert</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a married
woman. See <er>Covert</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, 3.</cd> -- <col><b>Feme
sole</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a single or unmarried woman; a
woman who has never been married, or who has been divorced, or whose
husband is dead.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>Feme sole trader</b></col>
<it>or</it> <col><b>Feme sole merchant</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Eng.
Law)</fld>, <cd>a married woman, who, by the custom of London, engages
in business on her own account, inpendently of her
husband.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Femeral</ent>⟦br⟧
